			<h2>Uploading</h2>
			<p>One of the goals was to break the dependency from YouTube however bandwidth is still expensive and transferring large amounts of data does not come cheap. So the costs to provide my own videos to viewers is sadly too-high for me to handle. Due to this I've shifted my focus to creating the site/features around the videos but still allow me to host the video elsewhere (or on my own servers in the future). </p>

			<p>What this means is, I won't worry about the behind the scenes part of making the videos ready for viewers (often called encoding or processing of videos). I'll let YouTube handle it until I figure out a way to make my own servers able to handle it. </p>

			<p>So when the site is ready, the 'uploading' will be something I plug a YT video link into and it'll set it up into a REALLY nice format for everyone </p>
